Chrysopodes (Chrysopodes) spinellus was reported from Argentina (with larval description) (
Gonzalez Olazo and Heredia 2010
); however, the species identification in that report appears to be in error. The larva (L3) that was illustrated had a darkened head like both Chrysopodes (Chrysopodes) divisus and Chrysopodes (Chrysopodes) lineafrons , and it lacked the longitudinally elongate, separate mesal and lateral epicranial markings of Chrysopodes (Chrysopodes) spinellus . The illustrations more closely resemble Chrysopodes (Chrysopodes) divisus than Chrysopodes (Chrysopodes) lineafrons .
